HTML (Add data-category properly)
html
Copy code
<a class="nav-link text-nav-color border-bottom border-primary fw-bold" 
   data-category="0" 
   onclick="showCategory(0, 'All')">
   All
</a>

@foreach (var category in Model)
{
    <a class="nav-link text-nav-color" 
       data-category="@category.CategoryId" 
       onclick="showCategory(@category.CategoryId, '@category.CategoryName')">
       @category.CategoryName
    </a>
}
Note: I gave border-bottom border-primary fw-bold only to All initially.

2. JS → Update this part in showCategory() function:
javascript
Copy code
// Remove active style from all
$(".nav-link").removeClass("text-primary border-bottom border-primary fw-bold").addClass("text-nav-color");

// Add active style to selected
$(`[data-category="${categoryId}"]`)
    .removeClass("text-nav-color")
    .addClass("text-primary border-bottom border-primary fw-bold");
Final Result:
Case	Output
Page Load	All → Highlighted & Underlined
Click any Category	That one → Highlighted & Underlined, rest normal
